<page>
   <topic>FILE.DRIVE_TYPE Function</topic>
   
  <description>Returns The type of the drive.</description>   
   <syntax>Drive_Type as C = Drive_Type(C Drive)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>Drive_Type</name>
         <description>Valid types are:
</description><list>
<item><name>
"Removable"
</name></item><item><name>
"Fixed"
</name></item><item><name>
"CD-ROM"
</name></item><item><name>
"Remote" </name></item></list>
     </argument>
     
<argument>     
    
     <name>Drive
</name>
    <description>The letter of the drive.
</description>
     
</argument>     
   </arguments>
 
   <discussion>
The FILE.DRIVE_TYPE() method returns the type of Drive.
   </discussion>
  
   <sections>
       <section><title>Example</title>
            <description>Type the following in the Interactive window:</description>
            <example><![CDATA[
file.drive_type("a:") -> "Removable"
file.drive_type("c:") -> "Fixed"
file.drive_type("g:") -> "CD-ROM"
file.drive_type("A:\") ? ERROR  '(because \" has a special meaning in Alpha Anywhere. The backspace character is used to define quotes within a quoted string.)
file.drive_type("A:\ ") -> "Removable"
]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
